# Architecture (strict)

## How the rules connect

| Topic | Rule file |
| --- | --- |
| Feature folders, types, app thin routes | **This file** |
| One component per `*.tsx`, helper file placement | **react-one-component-per-file** |
| No barrel-only `index.ts` re-exports | **no-barrel-index** |
| shadcn, ai-elements, Lucide, styling | **ui-shadcn-lucide** |
| Prisma / migrations | **prisma-migrations** |
| Zod for runtime validation of unknown shapes | **zod-validation** |
| `import "server-only"` on server actions, repositories, Prisma client | **server-only-guard** |

## Standard UI library (read-only)

- **Do not modify** any files under **`src/components/ui/`** or **`src/components/ai-elements/`**. Treat them as a fixed standard library (shadcn + ai-elements), same as vendor code.
- **Customize only outside those folders:** compose in `src/features/...`, thin wrappers, `className` / props from parents, theme tokens in global styles—not edits inside `ui` or `ai-elements`. (More detail: **ui-shadcn-lucide**.)

## Feature ownership

- **All product/feature logic lives under `src/features/<feature-name>/`** (hooks, components, utils, types, constants specific to that feature).
- **`src/app/`** stays thin: routing, layouts, and wiring that imports from `src/features` (or shared libs). Do not grow heavy UI or business logic in route files—extract to a feature.
- **Shared cross-feature code** goes in `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/` (only if truly shared), or small shared modules—not inside a single feature folder unless it is feature-private.

## Colocation

- Group by slice: `components/`, `hooks/`, `utils/`, `types/`, `constants/`, `repositories/`, etc. Avoid a flat dump of unrelated files at the feature root.
- **Components** that need dedicated helpers use a **named subfolder** under `components/` (see **react-one-component-per-file**), or feature-level `utils/` when shared across several components in that feature.
- **Types** are not inlined in components or implementation `.ts` files (see Types below).

## Types (strict)

- **Never define feature or domain types inside `.tsx` or implementation `.ts` files** (components, hooks, utils). No `interface`/`type` blocks for shared props, models, or API shapes next to implementation—extract them.
- **Use dedicated files only:** `types.ts`, `*.types.ts`, or a `types/` folder within the feature (e.g. `src/features/chat/types/message.types.ts`).
- **Shared types** (used in more than one feature): **`src/global.types.ts` only**—one canonical file. Import with `from "@/global.types"`.
- **Runtime validation** of unknown structured data (JSON from storage, APIs, etc.) uses **Zod** in dedicated **`schemas/`** files—see **zod-validation**.

## TypeScript and lint discipline (strict)

- **Minimize casting and assertions.** Avoid `as …`, `as unknown as …`, and non-null `!` to force types. Prefer narrowing, type guards, and validated boundaries. Literal `as const` for readonly tuples/literals is fine when it improves inference.
- **No suppressions in source.** Do not add `eslint-disable`, `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error`, or `@ts-nocheck` in app or feature files. Fix the code or adjust **project** ESLint/TS config.

## Single responsibility

- **One main concern per file.** Split large UIs into smaller components (each in its own `*.tsx` per **react-one-component-per-file**); extract pure helpers to `utils` / `*.utils.ts` in the same feature.
- **Reuse deliberately:** import from `src/components/ui` and `src/components/ai-elements` (read-only); do not copy-paste their internals into features.

## SOLID (practical)

- **S** — Each module does one job (UI vs data vs formatting).
- **O** — Extend via composition/props/hooks rather than editing unrelated modules for every change.
- **L** — Substitute implementations via clear props/contracts.
- **I** — Small, focused props and hook return shapes.
- **D** — Depend on `lib` APIs and feature modules; import concrete files (no barrel-only `index.ts`—see **no-barrel-index**).

## Example layout

```text
src/
  global.types.ts          # app-wide shared types only
  features/chat/
    components/
      chat/                # optional folder: one main component + its utils
        chat.tsx
        chat.utils.ts
      chat-session/
        chat-session.tsx
        chat-session.utils.ts
    hooks/
    utils/                 # feature-wide helpers
    types/
    schemas/               # Zod schemas (runtime validation)
    repositories/
```
